notesStmt.note: Se'adyah ben Shelomoh: probably a compiler of this manuscript: inscribed, folio 61r. The Judeo-Arabic sentence at the end of Deuteronomy, folio 189v, implies that the author had employed a copyist.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrashim in Hebrew and Arabic on Leviticus, Numbers and Deuteronomy, followed by a short midrashic commentary on the Hafṭarot.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 34; written lines: 34; Catchwords on every verso. Titles written in larger characters.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 1422.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Fischl Hirsch: purchased by the British Library from him on 12 January 1877: inscribed, folio [208v].
